Program: Discovery
Title: The link between red hair and skin cancer
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwjm
Last Broadcast Date: 27 October 1995
The reason why red-haired people are prone to skin cancer. Scientists have found that those with red hair often have a genetic defect which stops their skin from tanning. Also in the programme, our oldest worm ancestor discovered in China and the amazing speed at which continents were formed. Presenter: Pauline Newman. Show less